    <div class="container" style="margin-top:50px">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
          <br />
          <h1><big class="text-uppercase">Support Rational Food Research</big>
          <br />
          <small>What are genetically-modified organisms (GMOs)?</small>
          </h1>
          <br />
        </div> 
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5 text-justify">
          <big>
          <p>As defined by the World Health Organization, genetically-modified organisms, or GMOs,
          are organisms in which the DNA has been artificially modified. This may sound scary, 
          but gene editing has been rigorously studied by scientists for decades. In fact, this technology has already been used to make our food more drought-tolerant, pest-resistant, and nutritious!</p>

          <p>Unfortunately, groups like the Non-GMO Project are stifling efforts to continue this research and meet the world's caloric and nutritional needs, especially as population numbers rise and the climate changes. <strong>Speak out, and let companies know that you support  efforts to improve our food.</strong></p>

          <small><p>Watch the video on the right from <a href="http://kurzgesagt.org/">Kurgesagt</a> for a more detailed breakdown.</p></small>
          </big>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <iframe class="center-block" width="640.5" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7TmcXYp8xu4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr>

      <form action='/send'>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <h3>Speak Out</h3>
          
            <label for="company">Select companies to email</label>
            <!--<button type="button" class="btn btn-default" id='check_all'>Select all</button>-->
            <div class="form-group" style="max-height:120px;overflow:auto"> 
              <div class="checkbox">
                <label><input type="checkbox" id="check_all">Select all</label>
              </div>
              <% for (company in companyNames) {%>
                <div class="checkbox">
                  <label><input type="checkbox" name="company" value= <%=company%> > <%=companyNames[company]%> </label>
                </div>
              <%} %>
            </div>

            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="subject">Subject</label>
              <input type="text" class="form-control" name="subject" id="subject" value="Support rational food research">
            </div>

            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="email">Editable text</label>
              <textarea class="form-control" rows="14" name="body" id="body">
I have been a long-time buyer of {company}. However, I have recently noticed that {company} includes a sticker from the "Non-GMO Project". This is deeply disturbing to me, and I have discontinued purchase of {company's} products as a result.

To date, no study has ever shown negative effects from the consumption of GMOs. Indeed, perpetuating the myth that GMOs are inherently less healthy than non-GMOs is damaging to the continued research efforts to end hunger and nutrient-deficiency around the world.

I urge {company} to remove the "Non-GMO Project" sticker from their products and support food research that will keep the world's population healthy and well-fed in the generations to come. I really enjoy {company}, but cannot, in good conscience, purchase goods or recommend products from companies that prop up fraudulent claims that impede scientific progress.
              </textarea>
            </div>
        </div>

